==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catkin
<hw>Cat"kin</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧t"k⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Cat</ets> + <ets>-kin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An
ament; a species of inflorescence, consisting of a slender axis with
many unisexual apetalous flowers along its sides, as in the willow and
poplar, and (as to the staminate flowers) in the chestnut, oak, hickory,
etc. -- so called from its resemblance to a cat's tail. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Ament</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>catkinate</ent>⟦br⟧
